## SECTION B — Java / Spring Boot

### B1 — Package structure matches SPEC §5
```
dev.queriva
├── QuerivaApplication.java
├── search/
│   ├── SearchController.java
│   ├── SearchRequest.java       ← record
│   ├── SearchResponse.java      ← record
│   ├── SearchHit.java           ← record
│   ├── SearchFilters.java       ← record
│   ├── QueryEmbeddingService.java
│   ├── QdrantSearchService.java
│   ├── LLMSynthesisService.java
│   └── SearchResultMapper.java
└── ingest/
    ├── IngestController.java
    ├── IngestRequest.java       ← record
    ├── IngestResponse.java      ← record
    ├── IngestService.java
    ├── ChunkingService.java
    ├── Chunk.java               ← record
    └── CollectionManager.java
```

### B2 — DTOs are Java records
No Lombok on DTOs. Use compact constructors for defaults.

```java
public record SearchRequest(
    @NotBlank String query,
    @NotBlank String collection,
    @Min(1) @Max(100) int topK,
    double minScore,
    String mode,
    SearchFilters filters
) {
    public SearchRequest {
        if (topK == 0) topK = 10;
        if (minScore == 0.0) minScore = 0.60;
        if (mode == null || mode.isBlank()) mode = "search";
    }
}
```

### B3 — Constructor injection only
No `@Autowired` on fields. All dependencies via constructor.

### B4 — No @Transactional unless explicitly needed
Qdrant is not JPA-transactional. Do not add `@Transactional` by default.

### B5 — HTTP clients have explicit timeouts and one retry
- Connect timeout: 5s
- Read timeout: 30s (Ollama can be slow)
- One retry on 5xx or IOException
- No retry on 4xx

### B6 — Bean Validation on all controllers
`@Valid` on every `@RequestBody`. Never validate manually in controller body.

### B7 — Controllers return ResponseEntity
```java
// GOOD
public ResponseEntity<SearchResponse> search(@Valid @RequestBody SearchRequest req) {
    return ResponseEntity.ok(searchService.search(req));
}
```

### B8 — One GlobalExceptionHandler via @ControllerAdvice
All uncaught exceptions handled in one place. No try/catch in controllers.
Controllers contain only: validation → service call → response mapping.

### B9 — Latency via System.nanoTime(), never estimated
```java
long start = System.nanoTime();
float[] vector = queryEmbeddingService.embed(query, model);
long embedMs = TimeUnit.NANOSECONDS.toMillis(System.nanoTime() - start);
```

### B10 — No @SuppressWarnings without explanation
```java
@SuppressWarnings("unchecked") // safe: Qdrant payload always List<String> here
```

