## SECTION D — TypeScript / React

### D1 — Strict TypeScript, no any
`tsconfig.json`: `"strict": true`. Use `unknown` + type guards, not `any`.

### D2 — API types in src/types/api.ts, derived from SPEC §6
Never inline API shapes in components. One source of truth.

### D3 — Named props interfaces, not inline types
```typescript
interface ResultCardProps {
  title: string;
  score: number;
  snippet: string;
  language: string;
  source: string;
  publishedAt: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
}
```

### D4 — No inline styles except dynamic values
Dynamic only (e.g. score bar width). All other styling via CSS variables
or className.

### D5 — Custom hooks for all data fetching
No fetch calls in component bodies. All API calls in `src/hooks/`.

### D6 — useReducer for complex state, useState for simple
`useSearch`: useReducer. `ModeToggle`, `FilterChip`: useState.

### D7 — UI strings as constants in src/constants/ui.ts
No hardcoded strings in JSX.

### D8 — Accessibility
Icon-only buttons: `aria-label`. Decorative icons: `aria-hidden="true"`.
Search input: associated `<label>` (visually hidden is OK).

### D9 — Explicit loading, error, empty states in every component
```typescript
if (loading) return <SearchSkeleton />;
if (error)   return <ErrorBanner message={error} />;
if (!results.length) return <EmptyState query={query} />;
return <ResultsList results={results} />;
```

### D10 — SearchWidget functional with only apiUrl + collection
All other props are optional with documented defaults.

