## SECTION E — Security

### E1 — No secrets in logs
Never log API keys, auth tokens, or user query content at INFO level.
Query text may be logged at DEBUG level only.

```java
// BAD
logger.info("Searching collection {} with query: {}", collection, query);
// GOOD
logger.info("Searching collection {} ({} results)", collection, results.size());
logger.debug("Query text: {}", query); // DEBUG only
```

### E2 — Input length limits on all endpoints
Query string: max 1000 characters.
Document body: max 100,000 characters (100KB).
Collection name: max 64 characters, alphanumeric + underscore only.
Reject with 400 if exceeded — never truncate silently.

```java
public record SearchRequest(
    @NotBlank @Size(max = 1000) String query,
    @NotBlank @Pattern(regexp = "^[a-zA-Z0-9_]{1,64}$") String collection,
    ...
) {}
```

### E3 — Path traversal prevention in file loader
The ingest-cli `file_loader.py` must resolve and validate all file paths
before reading. Reject any path that escapes the specified source directory.

```python
def safe_path(base_dir: str, user_path: str) -> Path:
    resolved = Path(base_dir).resolve() / user_path
    if not str(resolved).startswith(str(Path(base_dir).resolve())):
        raise ValueError(f"Path traversal detected: {user_path}")
    return resolved
```

### E4 — URL allowlist or validation in url_loader
The `url_loader.py` must not fetch private network addresses (localhost,
10.x.x.x, 192.168.x.x, 172.16-31.x.x). Reject with a clear error.

```python
import ipaddress, socket

def is_safe_url(url: str) -> bool:
    host = urllib.parse.urlparse(url).hostname
    try:
        ip = ipaddress.ip_address(socket.gethostbyname(host))
        return not (ip.is_private or ip.is_loopback or ip.is_link_local)
    except Exception:
        return False
```

### E5 — Qdrant filter injection prevention
Never build Qdrant filter conditions from raw user string concatenation.
Always use the typed Qdrant client filter builder.

```java
// BAD
String filterJson = "{\"must\":[{\"key\":\"language\",\"match\":{\"value\":\"" + lang + "\"}}]}";

// GOOD
Filter filter = Filter.newBuilder()
    .addMust(Condition.newBuilder()
        .setFieldCondition(FieldCondition.newBuilder()
            .setKey("language")
            .setMatch(Match.newBuilder().setKeyword(lang))))
    .build();
```

### E6 — Dependency versions are pinned exactly

Java (`pom.xml`): use exact versions, no ranges.
```xml
<!-- BAD -->
<version>[1.0,2.0)</version>
<!-- GOOD -->
<version>1.9.4</version>
```

Python (`requirements.txt`): pin exact versions.
```
# BAD
httpx>=0.27
# GOOD
httpx==0.27.0
```

Node (`package.json`): exact versions, no `^` or `~`.
```json
// BAD
"react": "^18.3.1"
// GOOD
"react": "18.3.1"
```

### E7 — Heavy ML dependencies belong only in embed-sidecar
`torch`, `transformers`, `sentence-transformers` are allowed only in
`packages/embed-sidecar/requirements.txt`.
`ingest-cli` must not import any ML libraries — it calls the sidecar API.

