## SECTION F — Architecture

### F1 — Layers do not skip levels
```
Controller → Service → Repository/Client
```
Controllers never call Qdrant directly.
Services never format HTTP responses.
Mappers never contain business logic.

### F2 — No circular dependencies between packages
`api` calls `embed-sidecar` via HTTP.
`ingest-cli` calls `api` via HTTP.
`ui` calls `api` via HTTP.
No package imports code from another package at build time.

### F3 — Feature flags via environment variables
Incomplete features gated with env var, not commented-out code.
```java
@Value("${features.rag.enabled:true}")
private boolean ragEnabled;
```

### F4 — Health checks actively verify dependencies
`GET /api/health` calls each dependency. Never return `"ok"` without
actively verifying Qdrant, Ollama, and embed-sidecar.

### F5 — Config documented at point of use
Every `@Value` or `os.getenv` references the SPEC section and env key.
```java
// SPEC §13: SEARCH_MIN_SCORE — default 0.60
@Value("${search.min-score:0.60}")
private double defaultMinScore;
```
